 Charles Moore, author of 'Not For 
Turning', the first volume of the only authorized biography of 
former British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher, offers new 
insights into Thatcher's leadership. Thatcher granted Moore 
access to hundreds of previously unseen documents. Moore talks 
with Bloomberg's Kathleen Hays and Vonnie Quinn on Bloomberg 
Radio's "The Hays Advantage."   (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 18:28
 